'''Gurdwara Toka Sahib''' is an historical [[Sikh]] shrine located at ''Toka'' village, near [[Naraingarh]] in [[Haryana]]. <ref>[http://www.worldgurudwaras.com/sirmour/gurudwara-toka-sahib-toka Gurdwara Toka Sahib at Worldgurudwaras.com] </ref> In 1688, [[Guru Gobind Singh]] visited this area from his way from [[Paunta Sahib]] to [[Anandpur Sahib]]. Lieutenant Fateh Singh served as president of place for 13 years.<ref>[http://www.thesikhencyclopedia.com/historic-gurdwaras-outside-punjab/toka-sahib-gurdwara thesikhencyclopedia]: Retrieved information of Gurdwara Toka Sahib</ref><ref>''Biography of Fateh Singh'': Balwinder Singh. Retrieved from Labana Sewak, January 2005</ref>

